                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-171-off919 t18120916-171-crimeloc922"></join>; the Yorkshire Grey.</p>
               <p>Q. On the 21st of July, did you lose any candlesticks - A. I did; they were at the back of the bar. The prisoner came in the tap and called for half a pint of beer, and when the prisoner left the house, my man said, that man has got some candlesticks. I pursued him and brought him back; he took the candlesticks out of his breeches. These are the candlesticks; I am sure they are mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in distress.</p>
               <p>
